<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>AHCECR305 · Collect Native Seed · Complete Learning Ecosystem</title>
    <!-- Font Awesome 6 -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css">
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }
        
        :root {
            --primary-dark: #0f3b2c;
            --primary-medium: #1d5e45;
            --primary-light: #4a8b6e;
            --accent-gold: #f5b342;
            --accent-soft: #fff2db;
            --bg-light: #f3faf3;
            --text-dark: #1a3326;
            --border-light: #c5e0c5;
            --card-shadow: 0 20px 40px -10px rgba(0, 40, 0, 0.2);
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', 'Segoe UI', Roboto, system-ui, sans-serif;
            background: #d9ead9;
            color: var(--text-dark);
            line-height: 1.7;
            padding: 1.5rem;
        }

        .master-ecosystem {
            max-width: 1800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 3rem;
            box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        /* ===== HERO SECTION ===== */
        .hero-banner {
            background: linear-gradient(165deg, #0a3625, #1b6b4c, #144d36);
            color: white;
            padding: 3.5rem 4rem;
            border-bottom: 12px solid var(--accent-gold);
            position: relative;
        }

        .hero-banner h1 {
            font-size: 4.2rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            letter-spacing: -0.02em;
            line-height: 1.2;
            text-shadow: 2px 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
        }

        .hero-banner h1 i {
            color: var(--accent-gold);
            margin-right: 20px;
            filter: drop-shadow(0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.3));
        }

        .hero-qual {
            display: flex;
            gap: 2.5rem;
            margin-top: 2rem;
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }

        .hero-qual span {
            background: rgba(255,255,240,0.15);
            backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
            padding: 0.6rem 1.8rem;
            border-radius: 60px;
            border-left: 5px solid var(--accent-gold);
            font-weight: 500;
        }

        /* ===== TABBED NAVIGATION ===== */
        .tab-bar {
            background: #154f34;
            padding: 0 3rem;
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 0.5rem;
            border-bottom: 3px solid #a8d0a8;
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            z-index: 1000;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0,20,0,0.2);
        }

        .tab {
            color: #e0f0da;
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            padding: 1.2rem 1.8rem;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-bottom: 4px solid transparent;
            transition: all 0.2s;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
            background: transparent;
            border: none;
            font-family: inherit;
        }

        .tab:hover {
            background: #216344;
            color: white;
        }

        .tab.active {
            color: white;
            border-bottom-color: var(--accent-gold);
            background: linear-gradient(transparent 60%, rgba(245,179,66,0.15) 100%);
        }

        .tab i {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
        }

        /* ===== MAIN TAB CONTENT AREA ===== */
        .tab-content {
            display: none;
            padding: 3rem 3.5rem;
            background: white;
            animation: fadeIn 0.5s ease;
        }

        .tab-content.active {
            display: block;
        }

        @keyframes fadeIn {
            from { opacity: 0.3; transform: translateY(10px); }
            to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
        }

        /* ===== CONTENT STYLING ===== */
        h2 {
            font-size: 2.8rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: var(--primary-dark);
            margin: 2rem 0 2rem 0;
            border-left: 20px solid var(--accent-gold);
            padding-left: 1.8rem;
            letter-spacing: -0.01em;
        }

        h2:first-of-type {
            margin-top: 0;
        }

        h3 {
            font-size: 2rem;
            font-weight: 650;
            color: #1b5a3a;
            margin: 2.5rem 0 1.5rem 0;
            border-bottom: 4px dashed #bfe0bf;
            padding-bottom: 0.7rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 15px;
        }

        h4 {
            font-size: 1.6rem;
            color: #154f31;
            margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
            font-weight: 650;
        }

        h5 {
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: #0f462f;
            margin: 1.5rem 0 0.8rem;
        }

        .card-deck {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
            gap: 2rem;
            margin: 2.5rem 0;
        }

        .info-card {
            background: var(--bg-light);
            border-radius: 2rem;
            padding: 2rem;
            border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
            box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(0,30,0,0.08);
            transition: transform 0.2s;
        }

        .info-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
            box-shadow: 0 20px 30px rgba(0,60,0,0.15);
        }

        .info-card i {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: var(--primary-medium);
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .legislation-panel {
            background: #eef5ee;
            border-radius: 2rem;
            padding: 2.5rem;
            margin: 2rem 0;
            border-left: 12px solid #2a6e5a;
            box-shadow: inset 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.02);
        }

        .act-list {
            columns: 2;
            column-gap: 3rem;
            margin: 1.5rem 0;
        }

        .act-item {
            break-inside: avoid;
            padding: 0.8rem;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 60px;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 12px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
        }

        .act-item i {
            color: var(--accent-gold);
            font-size: 1.4rem;
            width: 2rem;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .fruit-type-showcase {
            display: flex;
            gap: 2rem;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            margin: 2rem 0;
        }

        .fruit-pillar {
            flex: 1 1 250px;
            background: #f9fff9;
            border-radius: 2rem;
            padding: 2rem;
            text-align: center;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0,20,0,0.1);
            border: 2px solid transparent;
        }

        .fruit-pillar.A { border-top: 12px solid #c45d9b; }
        .fruit-pillar.B { border-top: 12px solid #d4a13e; }
        .fruit-pillar.C { border-top: 12px solid #7f9a6b; }

        .fruit-pillar h5 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
        .fruit-pillar ul { text-align: left; margin-top: 1.5rem; }

        /* ===== QUIZ STYLES ===== */
        .quiz-container {
            background: #1e3d2e;
            color: #fff8e7;
            border-radius: 2.5rem;
            padding: 2.5rem;
            margin: 3rem 0;
        }

        .quiz-question-card {
            background: #2d543a;
            border-radius: 1.8rem;
            padding: 2rem;
            margin: 2rem 0;
        }

        .quiz-question {
            font-size: 1.4rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }

        .quiz-option {
            background: #3f6a4a;
            margin: 0.8rem 0;
            padding: 1rem 2rem;
            border-radius: 60px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: all 0.1s;
            border: 2px solid transparent;
        }

        .quiz-option:hover {
            background: #568b5e;
            transform: scale(1.01);
        }

        .quiz-option input {
            margin-right: 1rem;
            transform: scale(1.2);
            accent-color: var(--accent-gold);
        }

        .quiz-feedback {
            display: none;
            margin-top: 1.5rem;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border-radius: 1rem;
            font-weight: 500;
        }

        .feedback-correct { background: #2f7d4f; }
        .feedback-incorrect { background: #a14f4f; }

        .btn {
            background: var(--accent-gold);
            color: #1a401a;
            border: none;
            font-weight: 700;
            padding: 1rem 2.5rem;
            border-radius: 60px;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: 0.2s;
            border: 2px solid transparent;
        }

        .btn:hover {
            background: #ffc55a;
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
        }

        .btn-outline {
            background: transparent;
            border: 3px solid var(--primary-medium);
            color: var(--primary-medium);
        }

        /* ===== CHECKLIST STYLES ===== */
        .checklist-super {
            background: white;
            border: 4px solid var(--primary-medium);
            border-radius: 2.5rem;
            padding: 2.5rem;
            margin: 2.5rem 0;
            box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
        }

        .checklist-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 1.2rem;
            margin: 2rem 0;
        }

        .checklist-item {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 1rem;
            padding: 0.8rem 1.2rem;
            background: #f0faf0;
            border-radius: 60px;
        }

        .checklist-item input[type="checkbox"] {
            width: 24px;
            height: 24px;
            accent-color: var(--primary-medium);
        }

        /* ===== TOOL TABLE ===== */
        .tool-matrix {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 2rem;
            overflow: hidden;
            box-shadow: 0 15px 30px rgba(0,20,0,0.1);
            margin: 2rem 0;
        }

        .tool-matrix th {
            background: var(--primary-medium);
            color: white;
            padding: 1.2rem;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
        }

        .tool-matrix td {
            padding: 1.2rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #c5e0c5;
            vertical-align: top;
        }

        .tool-matrix tr:last-child td {
            border-bottom: none;
        }

        /* ===== RISK MATRIX ===== */
        .risk-table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
        }

        .risk-table th {
            background: #154f34;
            color: white;
            padding: 1rem;
        }

        .risk-table td {
            border: 2px solid #b5d6b5;
            padding: 1rem;
            text-align: center;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .risk-low { background: #c8e6c8; }
        .risk-medium { background: #fff3b0; }
        .risk-high { background: #ffb5b5; }
        .risk-extreme { background: #ff8080; color: white; }

        /* ===== FOOTER ===== */
        .footer-expanded {
            background: #0f3829;
            color: #e0f0da;
            padding: 4rem;
            margin-top: 3rem;
            border-top: 8px solid var(--accent-gold);
        }

        .footer-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
            gap: 3rem;
        }

        @media (max-width: 1200px) {
            .footer-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
            .tab-bar { padding: 0 1rem; }
            .tab { padding: 1rem; }
            .hero-banner h1 { font-size: 3rem; }
        }

        /* ===== PRINT STYLES ===== */
        @media print {
            .tab-bar, .btn, .hero-banner { display: none; }
            .tab-content { display: block !important; }
            body { background: white; padding: 0; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="master-ecosystem">
        <!-- HERO SECTION -->
        <div class="hero-banner">
            <h1><i class="fas fa-seedling"></i> AHCECR305 · Collect Native Seed</h1>
            <div class="hero-qual">
                <span><i class="fas fa-certificate"></i> Certificate III in Conservation & Ecosystem Management</span>
                <span><i class="fas fa-clipboard-check"></i> Release 1 · 2026</span>
                <span><i class="fas fa-flask"></i> Florabank · NRE Tas · Understorey Network</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- EXPANDED TABBED NAVIGATION -->
        <div class="tab-bar">
            <button class="tab active" onclick="switchTab(event, 'tab1')"><i class="fas fa-balance-scale"></i> Legislation & Permits</button>
            <button class="tab" onclick="switchTab(event, 'tab2')"><i class="fas fa-map-signs"></i> Work Planning</button>
            <button class="tab" onclick="switchTab(event, 'tab3')"><i class="fas fa-search"></i> Species ID & Provenance</button>
            <button class="tab" onclick="switchTab(event, 'tab4')"><i class="fas fa-hand-holding-heart"></i> Collection Methods</button>
            <button class="tab" onclick="switchTab(event, 'tab5')"><i class="fas fa-leaf"></i> Sustainability & Ethics</button>
            <button class="tab" onclick="switchTab(event, 'tab6')"><i class="fas fa-broom"></i> Cleaning & Storage</button>
            <button class="tab" onclick="switchTab(event, 'tab7')"><i class="fas fa-clipboard-list"></i> Risk & WHS</button>
            <button class="tab" onclick="switchTab(event, 'tab8')"><i class="fas fa-puzzle-piece"></i> Quizzes & Games</button>
            <button class="tab" onclick="switchTab(event, 'tab9')"><i class="fas fa-print"></i> Printables</button>
        </div>

        <!-- ===== TAB 1: LEGISLATION & PERMITS (EXPANDED) ===== -->
        <div id="tab1" class="tab-content active">
            <h2>⚖️ Environmental Legislation & Permitting Framework</h2>
            
            <div class="legislation-panel">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-gavel"></i> Commonwealth & State Acts</h3>
                <div class="act-list">
                    <div class="act-item"><i class="fas fa-file-contract"></i> <strong>Environment Protection and Biodiversity Conservation Act 1999</strong> (EPBC) – Commonwealth, protects Matters of National Environmental Significance</div>
                    <div class="act-item"><i class="fas fa-file-contract"></i> <strong>Threatened Species Protection Act 1995</strong> (Tas) – listed species</div>
                    <div class="act-item"><i class="fas fa-file-contract"></i> <strong>Nature Conservation Act 2002</strong> (Tas) – protected wildlife</div>
                    <div class="act-item"><i class="fas fa-file-contract"></i> <strong>National Parks and Reserves Management Act 2002</strong></div>
                    <div class="act-item"><i class="fas fa-file-contract"></i> <strong>Crown Lands Act 1976</strong> – public land</div>
                    <div class="act-item"><i class="fas fa-file-contract"></i> <strong>Local Government Act</strong> – roadside vegetation</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>📋 Detailed Permit Requirements</h3>
            <div class="card-deck">
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-tree"></i>
                    <h4>National Parks & Reserves</h4>
                    <p>Permit required under <em>National Parks and Reserves Management Act 2002</em>. Apply to NRE Tas at least 4 weeks prior. Conditions include: maximum 20% collection, no damage to plants, reporting required.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-forest"></i>
                    <h4>State Forest & Forest Reserves</h4>
                    <p>Authority from Sustainable Timber Tasmania or relevant state forestry agency. May require research permit. Restrictions on threatened species.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-road"></i>
                    <h4>Roadside & Local Government</h4>
                    <p>Written permission from local council. Often requires traffic management plan and public liability insurance. Check council roadside vegetation guidelines.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-handshake"></i>
                    <h4>Private Property & Indigenous Lands</h4>
                    <p>Written landholder permission mandatory. For Indigenous lands, consult Traditional Owners/Custodians – may require cultural heritage assessment and benefit-sharing agreement.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>🔍 Case Study: Applying for a Scientific Permit in Tasmania</h3>
            <div style="background:#f5f9f5; border-radius:2rem; padding:2rem;">
                <ol style="margin-left:2rem;">
                    <li><strong>Identify purpose:</strong> restoration seed collection for Bushcare project</li>
                    <li><strong>Complete NRE Tas application form:</strong> include species list, quantities, location maps, collection methods, risk assessments</li>
                    <li><strong>Submit with supporting documents:</strong> landowner consent, CV of collector, insurance</li>
                    <li><strong>Processing time:</strong> 20 business days; may be referred to Threatened Species Section</li>
                    <li><strong>Conditions imposed:</strong> submit annual report, label all collections with permit number, allow inspection</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <h3>⚠️ Penalties for Unauthorized Collection</h3>
            <p>Fines up to $10,000 (individual) or $50,000 (corporation) under Tasmanian legislation. EPBC Act penalties for threatened species: up to 7 years imprisonment and/or $138,600 fine.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- ===== TAB 2: WORK PLANNING (EXPANDED) ===== -->
        <div id="tab2" class="tab-content">
            <h2>🗺️ Work Plan Development & Review</h2>
            
            <h3>1. Desktop Survey & Species Selection</h3>
            <div class="florabank-panel" style="background:#e3f1e3; border-radius:2rem; padding:2rem;">
                <h4>Florabank Guidelines: Essential Planning Steps</h4>
                <ul style="margin-left:2rem;">
                    <li><strong>Desktop survey:</strong> AVH, Atlas of Living Australia, regional vegetation guides, local council databases</li>
                    <li><strong>Species list refinement:</strong> consider seed storage behaviour (orthodox/recalcitrant), collection difficulty, quantity needed</li>
                    <li><strong>Phenology research:</strong> flowering and fruiting periods from herbarium records, previous collections (Australian Seed Bank Partnership)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h3>2. Work Plan Components (Detailed)</h3>
            <div class="checklist-super">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-check-double"></i> Mandatory Work Plan Elements</h4>
                <div class="checklist-grid">
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Species required:</strong> botanical name, common name, target quantity</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Location details:</strong> property name, reserve, GPS coordinates, access notes</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Timing:</strong> preferred collection window, backup dates, flowering status</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Permits:</strong> permit numbers attached, landholder permission letter</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Personnel:</strong> collector names, supervisor contact, emergency contacts</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Equipment list:</strong> collection tools, cleaning gear, PPE</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Transport & logistics:</strong> vehicle, cool storage, delivery arrangements</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Risk assessment:</strong> WHS and environmental hazards</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>3. Reconnaissance & Site Assessment</h3>
            <p>Conduct site visit during flowering to:</p>
            <ul style="margin-left:2rem;">
                <li>Confirm species presence and population size</li>
                <li>Assess plant health and seed crop potential</li>
                <li>Mark plants with GPS/flagging tape for later return</li>
                <li>Identify access issues, hazards, sensitive areas</li>
                <li>Check for nesting birds, threatened species habitat</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4. Work Plan Review Process</h3>
            <table class="tool-matrix">
                <tr><th>Review trigger</th><th>Action required</th><th>Documentation</th></tr>
                <tr><td>Weather changes</td><td>Delay collection if rain/fire risk; adjust drying plan</td><td>Note on work plan revision</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Phenology shift</td><td>Early/late ripening – adjust dates, may need new reconnaissance</td><td>Update collection schedule</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Access issues</td><td>Gate locked, road closed – contact landholder, find alternate site</td><td>Record in review section</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Species unavailable</td><td>Select alternative species meeting fruit type requirements</td><td>Seek supervisor approval</td></tr>
            </table>
        </div>

        <!-- ===== TAB 3: SPECIES ID & PROVENANCE (EXPANDED) ===== -->
        <div id="tab3" class="tab-content">
            <h2>🔬 Species Identification & Provenance</h2>
            
            <h3>Identification Tools & Resources</h3>
            <div class="card-deck">
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-book"></i>
                    <h4>Digital Floras</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>PlantNET (NSW Flora Online)</li>
                        <li>VicFlora (Victoria)</li>
                        <li>EUCLID (Eucalypts)</li>
                        <li>World Wide Wattle (Acacia)</li>
                        <li>Understorey Network Database (1800+ Tasmanian species)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-leaf"></i>
                    <h4>Herbarium Resources</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Australasian Virtual Herbarium (AVH) – 8 million specimens</li>
                        <li>State herbaria (HO – Tas, MEL – Vic, etc.)</li>
                        <li>Digital specimen images</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-camera"></i>
                    <h4>Field Guides & Apps</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>iNaturalist Australia</li>
                        <li>Local field guides (e.g., "Wildflowers of Tasmania")</li>
                        <li>Regional vegetation guides</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Provenance: The Science of Local Adaptation</h3>
            <div style="background:#fff2db; border-radius:2rem; padding:2rem; margin:2rem 0;">
                <h4>Why Provenance Matters</h4>
                <p>Plants collected from similar environmental conditions (rainfall, temperature, soil type, altitude) will have adapted to those conditions. Using local provenance seed increases survival rates in restoration projects by up to 300% (Florabank data).</p>
                <p><strong>Seed Transfer Zones:</strong> Many states have defined zones – collect within the same zone as planting site.</p>
            </div>

            <h3>Uncertain Species Protocol</h3>
            <div style="background:#dff0df; border-radius:2rem; padding:2rem;">
                <h4>Step-by-Step Voucher Collection</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Collect representative specimen: 30cm branch with leaves, flowers if possible, fruits</li>
                    <li>Press immediately in newspaper with cardboard, change papers daily</li>
                    <li>Photograph: whole plant, bark, leaves (upper/lower), flower close-up, fruit</li>
                    <li>Record: location (GPS), date, habitat, plant height, flower colour, abundance</li>
                    <li>Assign temporary ID (e.g., "Acacia sp. Freer Farm")</li>
                    <li>Submit to state herbarium for identification (may take weeks, fee applicable)</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <h3>Fruit Type Explorer (Interactive)</h3>
            <div class="fruit-type-showcase">
                <div class="fruit-pillar A">
                    <i class="fas fa-apple-alt" style="font-size:3rem; color:#c45d9b;"></i>
                    <h5>Fleshy Fruits (A)</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li><i>Billardiera longiflora</i> (climbing blueberry)</li>
                        <li><i>Tasmannia lanceolata</i> (mountain pepper)</li>
                        <li><i>Coprosma quadrifida</i> (native currant)</li>
                        <li><i>Astroloma humifusum</i> (cranberry heath)</li>
                        <li><i>Exocarpos cupressiformis</i> (native cherry)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="fruit-pillar B">
                    <i class="fas fa-seedling" style="font-size:3rem; color:#d4a13e;"></i>
                    <h5>Dry Dehiscent (B)</h5>
                    <ul>
