            <h3>Collection Quantity Calculations</h3>
            <div style="background:#f5f9f5; border-radius:2rem; padding:2rem;">
                <h4>How Much to Collect?</h4>
                <p><strong>Rule of thumb:</strong> collect 2-3 times the amount needed, accounting for:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Cleaning losses (chaff, empty seeds) – can be 30-80%</li>
                    <li>Viability testing failures</li>
                    <li>Storage/insurance buffer</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Example:</strong> Need 1000 viable seeds for nursery. Estimated cleaning loss 40%, viability 60% → collect approx 2,800 seeds (1000 / 0.6 / 0.6).</p>
            </div>
