        <!-- ===== TAB 5: SUSTAINABILITY & ETHICS ===== -->
        <div id="tab5" class="tab-content">
            <h2>♻️ Sustainable Collection Practices</h2>
            
            <h3>The 20% Rule: Scientific Basis</h3>
            <div style="background:#eef5ee; border-radius:2rem; padding:2rem;">
                <p>Research (Florabank) shows collecting <strong>no more than 20% of available seed</strong> from a population ensures:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Sufficient seed for natural regeneration</li>
                    <li>Maintenance of genetic diversity</li>
                    <li>Food source for native animals preserved</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Application:</strong> Visually estimate total seed crop, collect ≤20% from each plant. For small populations (<20 plants), collect from fewer plants or lower percentage.</p>
            </div>

            <h3>Ethical Collection Guidelines</h3>
            <div class="card-deck">
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-fire"></i>
                    <h4>Avoid Post-Fire Areas</h4>
                    <p>Plants regenerating after fire need all seeds for population recovery. Wait at least 2-3 years post-fire.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-paw"></i>
                    <h4>Protect Fauna</h4>
                    <p>Check for nests, hollows, feeding activity. Delay collection if birds are nesting in target plants. Leave seed on ground for ground-foragers.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-biohazard"></i>
                    <h4>Biosecurity Protocols</h4>
                    <p>Clean footwear, tools, vehicle tyres before entering and leaving site. Use 70% ethanol or 1% bleach solution. Prevents spread of Phytophthora, myrtle rust, weeds.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Environmental Impact Assessment (Template)</h3>
            <div class="checklist-super">
