        <div id="tab6" class="tab-content">
            <h2>🧹 Seed Cleaning & Storage Protocols</h2>
            
            <h3>Cleaning Methods by Fruit Type</h3>
            <table class="tool-matrix">
                <tr><th>Fruit Type</th><th>Cleaning Method</th><th>Equipment</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
                <tr><td>Fleshy (A)</td><td>Macerate, ferment, float off pulp</td><td>Bowl, sieve, water, food processor (gentle)</td><td>Remove all flesh to prevent mould</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Dry Dehiscent (B)</td><td>Thresh, sieve, winnow</td><td>Rubber mat, sieves (various), blower, wind tray</td><td>Separate seeds from capsules</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Dry Indehiscent (C)</td><td>Rub over sieve, air separation</td><td>Graded sieves, seed blower</td><td>Grasses – remove awns, chaff</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Cone-bearing (Banksia)</td><td>Oven heating to open cones</td><td>Oven (50-70°C), trays</td><td>Monitor temperature – don't cook seeds</td></tr>
            </table>

            <h3>Drying Protocols</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Air drying:</strong> Spread in single layer on newspaper/trays, room temperature (15-25°C), low humidity, good airflow. Turn daily.</li>
                <li><strong>Silica gel drying:</strong> For humid conditions, use sealed container with silica gel (ratio 1:1 seed:gel).</li>
                <li><strong>Moisture content target:</strong> Orthodox seeds 5-8% for storage; recalcitrant cannot be dried below 30-50%.</li>
                <li><strong>Testing dryness:</strong> Seed should crack/snap, not bend.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Storage Systems</h3>
            <div class="card-deck">
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-thermometer-half"></i>
                    <h4>Short-term (0-2 years)</h4>
                    <p>Airtight containers (glass jars, ziplock bags), cool dark cupboard (15-20°C). Add silica gel packets. Check monthly for mould/pests.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-snowflake"></i>
                    <h4>Long-term (2-20+ years)</h4>
                    <p>Dried seeds in sealed foil/glass, freezer (-18°C) or fridge (4°C). Use moisture-proof containers. Thaw before opening.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
                    <h4>Recalcitrant Seeds</h4>
                    <p>Cannot be stored long-term. Sow fresh, or store moist (not wet) with fungicide in fridge for weeks-months (e.g., rainforest species).</p>
                </div>
            </div>

